  "title": "Conductors - solid conducting sphere in ext field",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two cases of a conducting sphere of radius R between a pair of parallel plates that are a distance d apart from each other. In case 1, the left plate has a charge of positive Q and the right side is negatively charged. In case 2, the left plate has a charge of positive 2 Q and the right plate is negatively charged.\" src=\"/images/34d32d40ea310b72c99afb6e4266e84c.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two parallel plates are charged with equal amounts of charge but opposite sign and separated by a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction d over 2\"><math alttext=\"the fraction d over 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span>. A neutral, solid conducting sphere of radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R less than the fraction, d over 2\"><math alttext=\"R less than the fraction, d over 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>R</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>d</mi></mstyle><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span> is placed between the oppositely charged plates. In Case <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> there is a charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mstyle></math></span></span> on the positive plate. In Case <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> there is a charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive 2 Q\"><math alttext=\"positive 2 Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>Q</mi></mstyle></math></span></span> on the positive plate. Which of the following correctly compares the electric field <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E sub 1\"><math alttext=\"E sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> inside the sphere in Case <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> to the electric field <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E sub 2\"><math alttext=\"E sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> inside the sphere in Case <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i2",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E sub 2 equals one half E sub 1\"><math alttext=\"E sub 2 equals one half E sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span></p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E sub 2 equals E sub 1\"><math alttext=\"E sub 2 equals E sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span></p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E sub 2 equals 2 E sub 1\"><math alttext=\"E sub 2 equals 2 E sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span></p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The electric field cannot be determined without knowing the radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>R</mi></math></span></span> of the sphere relative to the plate separation distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d\"><math alttext=\"d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>d</mi></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
